						<summary>

						<p>This is dated the <hi rend="bold">6th year of</hi> the Chālukya king <hi rend="bold">Pratāpachakravarti-Jagadēkamalladēva,</hi> Rudhirōdgari (= <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1143-44</hi>), with no other details. The <hi rend="italic">Daṇḍanāyaka</hi> <hi rend="bold">Chīyamarasa</hi> is said to have made a grant of land for the service of the god Aṟeya-Śaṅkaradēva, consecrated by Sāvi-Gavuḍa and Śaṅkara-Gavuḍa. An oil-mill, a house and a garden are also said to have been granted.</p>						

						</summary>
